synopsis: After abandoning her four-year-old daughter in Lebanon to pursue a better life in Quebec, Sana cuts every link to her Lebanese ties and never looks back. That is until her daughter, now 21, shows up in Montreal for a visit. This film explores what it means to be free for a woman.
casting: ['Louise Portal', 'Renée Thomas', 'Leyla Hakim', 'Walid El-Alayli', 'Jean-François Blanchard', 'Mariloup Wolfe', 'Catherine Colvey', 'Sébastien Ricard', 'Ali El Khalil', 'Pierre Gemegian', 'Hélène Mercier']

synopsis: Four crazy antiheroes on the run. Their leader is the unworldly innocent, naive Marnie, a house cat who is not allowed to leave the house and only knows about real life from television
tagline: One gang of runaways. One secret mission. One pawsome adventure!
